OL,3,CA decade since Storm Abigail: Why does
OL,4,Cthe Met Office name storms?
OL,6,FOther countries have been naming
OL,7,Fstorms for hundreds of years.
OL,8,FHurricane Santa Ana was named by
OL,9,Fpeople in Puerto Rico after it hit the
OL,10,FCaribbean island on July 26, 1825.
OL,12,FThe Met Office names storms which are
OL,13,Fforecast to cause disruption or damage.
OL,15,FStorm names provide a reference point
OL,16,Ffor emergency services and helps
OL,17,Fcommunicate safety information to the
OL,18,Fpublic.
