OL,3,CA decade since Storm Abigail: Why does
OL,4,Cthe Met Office name storms?
OL,6,FData from the Met Office showed that
OL,7,Fduring Storm Eowyn in January 2025 99%
OL,8,Fof people within the red warning area
OL,9,Fwere aware of the warnings and 95% of
OL,10,Fthem took action, showing how
OL,11,Fbeneficial storm naming is.
OL,13,FWill Lang, Chief Meteorologist at the
OL,14,FMet Office said: "Storm naming is more
OL,15,Fthan a label, it's a public safety
OL,16,Ftool that makes severe weather easier
OL,17,Fto remember, talk about, and follow."
OL,19,FWho chooses the names?
